article.description: Jalen Pickett, Don Carey and Elijah Burns scored 19 points apiece as Siena topped Saint Bonaventure 78-65 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Trio leads Siena past St. Bonaventure 78-65
article.linkText: Trio leads Siena past St. Bonaventure 78-65
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Jalen Pickett, Don Carey and Elijah Burns scored 19 points apiece as Siena topped Saint Bonaventure 78-65 on Tuesday night. Manny Camper added 15 points and a career-high 17 rebounds for the Saints (2-1). Dominick Welch scored a career-best 21 points and had seven rebounds for the Bonnies (0-3). Kyle Lofton added 14 points and seven assists. Justin Winston scored 10. Siena shot 46% from the floor and made 22 of 29 free throws. St. Bonaventure shot 39% from the floor and hit all seven of its free throws. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
